c:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"5.6% efficiency loss from harsh cleaners"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Anti-reflective coatings permanently damaged"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Safe cleaning products exist, tests confirm"}]]}]]}]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Solar panel owners are paying to clean their modules—and in some cases, they're paying to break them. Researchers at ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.csp.fraunhofer.de/en.html","children":"Fraunhofer CSP"}]," in Germany just dropped a finding that should make every O&M manager pause: some widely-used cleaning agents are eating away at anti-reflective glass coatings, permanently degrading panel efficiency by up to 5.6%.\nThat's not a rounding error. On a commercial solar farm, a 5.6% loss translates to serious revenue erosion over a 25-year lifespan. The irony is thick: operators are literally paying to reduce their own yields.\nThe research, ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.pv-magazine.com/","children":"reported by PV Magazine"}],", tested multiple cleaning products and found a stark split. Some cleaners performed fine. Others caused visible, irreversible damage to the coating that's supposed to boost light absorption. The difference between \"safe\" and \"destructive\" wasn't obvious without testing—you can't tell by reading the label."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/when-solar-maintenance-cuts-your-output-by-5-6/subtitle.jpg","alt":"The maintenance industry's dirty secret","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"The maintenance industry's dirty secret"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Here's the reality gap: solar maintenance is often treated as a commodity service. Cleaning contracts go to the lowest bidder, and nobody asks what's in the bucket. Fraunhofer's work suggests that's a costly blind spot.\nFor module manufacturers, this adds another variable to warranty claims. If a coating fails prematurely, was it defective glass or the cleaning crew? For O&M providers, it's a differentiation opportunity—or a liability risk, depending on their product choices.\nThe practical signal is straightforward: if you're managing solar assets, you need to audit your cleaning protocols. The anti-reflective coating market is built on incremental efficiency gains; wiping those gains away with the wrong detergent is a self-inflicted wound.\nThere's no breakthrough press release here. Just a reminder that in hardware, maintenance isn't neutral—and the wrong \"care\" can cost more than neglect."}]]}]
